I"=<ol>
  <li>Heat the oven to 190°C. Heat 1 tbsp olive oil in a non-stick, lidded casserole. Brown the lamb all over then remove from the pan. Add the aubergine and another tablespoon of oil and cook until browned and softened a bit. Scoop out the aubergine then add the onion and garlic and cook until softened.</li>
  <li>Add the lamb and Egpplant with the Harissa, tomatoes and stock. Bring to a simmer then put on a lid and cook in the oven for 1½ hours until the lamb and aubergine are tender. Stir in the parsley and lemon. Good with new potatoes or rice.</li>
</ol>
